    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-16T18:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-16T18:43:00-05:00" n="1050"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1050">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">774.5/12–1652: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1050<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1050fn1">Also sent to London as telegram 4050 and to
                        Khartoum as telegram 16.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-16T18:43:00-05:00"
                            >December 16, 1952—6:43 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1227. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1171 to Cairo Dec 5 concerning
                    proposed Anglo-Amer talks on Egypt Rep Brit Emb Dec 15 informed along fol lines:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> wld like start these talks as
                            soon as possible after Christmas. Scope of talks (as Dept has suggested)
                            wld be: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“1. Terms upon which Her Majesty’s govt cld agree to withdraw
                                    from CZ, 2. collaboration of Arab states with <gloss
                                        target="#t_MEDO1">MEDO</gloss>, 3. mil aid to Egypt as part
                                    of gen settlement, 4. econ aid to Egypt.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>“Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> wld greatly prefer them
                            to take place in London, since the relevant info is all readily avail
                            there and since it is after all the Brit who will be putting forward
                            their ideas on the mil side at any rate.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
